dataset.title: March 2016 Tornadoes
dataset.description: Two tornadoes were spotted in Peoria County, Illinois on March 15, 2016.  One tornado was an EF-2 and had a damage path of 7.6 miles.  The second tornado was an EF-0 with a damage path of 3.83 miles.  Numerous structures and trees were damaged from this super cell storm.  This map displays the tornado paths and damage locations.

dataset.title: 2008 Orthophotography
dataset.description:
Peoria County contracted with the The Sanborn Map Company to receive aerial imagery during spring leaf-off in 2008.  The aerial imagery covers the Peoria County boundary extent with resolutions of one foot in rural areas and six inches in the Peoria metro area.  The data is available for download in zip file format.  The zip file contains aerial imagery in a MrSID compressed format per township boundary area extent, one county-wide aerial mosaic in MrSID format, and a shapefile of township boundaries.  The shapefile of township boundaries was used to create the MrSID aerials by township boundary area extent.  Please contact us if you would like a copy of the data.


Additional Metadata
Digital Photo Scale:  
  • 1" = 833' for the urban project area .
  • 1" = 1667' for the rural project area.
  • Alternate: 1" = 833' for the entire project area.
Project Size:  629 plus the 750ft buffer area.

Sun Angle:  Greater than 30 degrees above the horizon.

Spacing:  Full stereoscopic coverage.

Endlap:  60 percent, 80 percent in commercial areas.

Sidelap:  30 percent, 60 percent in commercial areas.

Crab:  Less than 3 degrees between and within any photo.

Tilt:  Less than 3% any photo, less than 5% between photos.

Flight Height Above Ground:  3,900'.

Image Type:  Color and Color IR.

Contact Information

Peoria County GIS
Email:  gis@peoriacounty.org
Phone:  309-495-4840

The aerial imagery is bound to the  Peoria County GIS Open Data License Agreement which can be found here:  https://data-peoriacountygis.opendata.arcgis.com/pages/peoria-county-gis-open-data-license-agreement.

dataset.title: 2019 Orthophotos by Township
dataset.description:
The Tri-County Regional Planning Commission, on behalf of local government partners Logan County, Peoria County, Tazewell County, and Woodford County oversaw a digital orthophotography acquisition project. The color digital orthrophotography was flown by Pictometry International Corp. in 2019 during the Spring leaf-off (<30%) period covering project area boundaries of Logan County, Peoria County, Tazewell County, and Woodford County. 

Please contact us if you would like a copy of the data.  The orthophotography available is within the Peoria County boundary only.  The orthophotography is composed of one single image per township boundary within Peoria County with a resolution of 6-inch GSD.  All images are in MrSID format with a total file size of 12GB-13GB.  *Note:  This is the second and final delivery with corrections applied from the vendor as of March 3, 2020. 

Contact Information

Peoria County GIS

Email:  gis@peoriacounty.org

Phone:  309-495-4840

The data can be downloaded here:  https://www.dropbox.com/sh/a3m1r47usbbq0ad/AABhtuMpzUmLrkmWxIK6peF7a?dl=0

The aerial imagery is bound to the  Peoria County GIS Open Data License Agreement which can be found here:  https://data-peoriacountygis.opendata.arcgis.com/pages/peoria-county-gis-open-data-license-agreement.

dataset.title: LIDAR Data
dataset.description:
This zip file contains LIDAR, Digital Terrain Models (DTM's), surface, and breakline datasets covering the extent of Peoria County.  The LIDAR data was captured during spring leaf-off in 2008.  There are eight databases in Esri's file geodatabase format which are broken down by eight areas in the County.  The DTM's conform to the ASPRS Class I Standards using the Illinois State Plane West coordinate system.  Please contact us if you would like a copy of the data.

More recent LIDAR data for Peoria County, IL was captured in 2012 by the State of Illinois through the Illinois Height Modernization Program (ILHMP).  Please click Here to read about the program and data available for download.

dataset.description: The Peoria County, Illinois airport runways were updated by Leading Edge Geomatics and the Peoria County GIS - IT Services Department in November 2021. The dataset was screen digitized using 6 inch resolution orthophotography which was captured during the spring of 2019 by Pictometry International Corp.  Original data was compiled by Sanborn Mapping Company in 2008.
